    "Accuracy refers to the overall performance measurement, specifically the total number of correct predictions made.",
    "Accuracy = (TP+TN) (TP+TN+FP+FN).",
    "Precision refers to the proportion of correctly predicted positive observations out of the total predicted positive observations.",
    "Precision = TP (TP+FP).",
    "Recall (sensitivity) refers to the proportion of correctly predicted positive observations to all observations in the current actual class."
